== Python

.Task
****
Assume a single command-line argument, a non-negative integer $n$.

Write a python script named `euler-20-factorial-digit-sum.py` which writes the sum of the digits in the number $n!$ to standard output.

Upload your solution to https://euler.computing.dcu.ie/einstein/[_Einstein_].
****

.Example invocation
----
$ python3 euler-20-factorial-digit-sum.py 10
----

.Example standard output
----
27
----

.Explanation
****
$10! = 10 * 9 * 8 ... * 2 * 1 = 3628800$, and the sum of digits is 3, 6, 2, 8, 8, 0 and 0 is 27.
